The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 10: Double-digit growth in passenger cars and motorcycles sales helped the domestic automobile sector grow 19.8 per cent at 757,188 units last month compared with 632,123 in May 2004. While domestic sales grew 19.8 per cent to 694,673 units, exports rose 19 per cent to 62,515 units, the Society of Indian Automobile Manufacturers said today.

 New Delhi, June 10: Jindal Steel amp; Power today said it has acquired 17 crore shares of Jindal Power for Rs 170 crore to make the power venture its subsidiary. With this, Jindal Steel?s shareholding in the latter has gone up to 99.62 per cent, Jindal Steel told the BSE.

 New Delhi, June 10: Eight states, which have not implemented the value added tax (VAT) regime, will yield to the new tax system under the pressure of economic forces, said Parthasarthy Shome, adviser to the finance minister. 

 New Delhi, June 10: Tata Steel has signed an agreement with the International Finance Corporation to avail of a $300-million loan to fund its future projects. 

 Mumbai, June 10: M.V. Nair, executive director of Dena Bank, has been appointed as chairman-cum-managing director. The appointment is for five years. Nair took charge on June 10.




